<promed@promedmail.org>
[EU's ADNS tables on avian influenza surveillance in wild birds for
2006 and the new table for 2007 [as of 5 Feb 2007] have been updated
earlier this week
(<http://ec.europa.eu/food/animal/diseases/adns/index_en.htm>).
No positive case has been found in the 14 surveyed countries since
the 2nd week of August 2006. In order to evaluate the significance of
the results, it would help to know how many wild birds have been
tested in each of the countries since August 2006. - Mod.AS]
